  "title": "Shipping Assistant #76914",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Container Trucking Service Provider</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Shipping Assistant</strong></li><li>Working Location: Central (Nearest MRT: Little India)</li><li>Working Hours: 5 days (Monday to Friday: 9 am-6 pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Up to SGD 2700 + AWS + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage all import/export documentation for sea and air freight, including the preparation of required shipping paperwork</li><li>Prepare invoices, permits, and arrange cargo insurance as needed</li><li>Liaise with clients for certificate applications and related documentation</li><li>Coordinate with shipping lines and freight forwarders to arrange container transshipments and confirm vessel schedules for barge connections</li><li>Submit Bill of Lading drafts to shipping lines or freight forwarders and print original Bills of Lading via online platforms</li><li>Apply for and process various permits using Tradeweb and handle back-to-back Certificate of Origin applications</li><li>Submit complete documentation packages to banks for DIP, D/A, and L/C transactions.</li><li>Scan and file documents into the in-house server system</li><li>Prepare local delivery documents and liaise with clients to coordinate delivery arrangements.</li><li>Coordinate with the warehouse on goods collection and delivery logistics</li><li>Monitor shipping line nominations for transshipment containers and update import container records in the in-house system</li><li>Coordinate with transporters for LCL clearances from ports to clients’ warehouses and assign transportation jobs as needed</li><li>Provide support for any other ad hoc assignments as required</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Min. O level</li><li>Min. 1 year of working experience in shipping documentation</li><li>Experience in import/export documentation or Tradenet/Tradeweb for permit processing is a plus</li><li>Training provided to inexperienced candidate</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#76914 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
